## 5. Cross-cutting: Context-gates-everything and buggify

- **Context gates everything.** Actors receive all nondeterminism (clock, spawn, rng,
  net) from `Context`. This pays off even with zero simulation: it makes every actor
  independently testable, mockable, and time-warpable in ordinary unit tests. The DST
  payoff is second-order; a more testable framework is the first-order win, and it is
  what justifies the refactor cost on its own.
- **A shared `buggify!()` hook.** murmer's own decision points become perturbable in sim
  (no-op in prod, seeded coin-flip in sim). appdata uses the same macro on its side and
  at the VFS boundary.

